# Data-Fetching Hook Pattern — iframe-app

Every resource gets exactly one "read" hook that folds all of TanStack
Query's states into one flat, predictable shape:

```ts
{ data, isLoading, isEmpty, isError, isOffline, error, refetch }
```

- `isEmpty` means the query succeeded but found nothing (e.g. Nominatim
  returned zero results) — distinct from `isError`.
- `isOffline` means a fetch failed but a previously-cached value for this
  exact query key still exists (`query.isError && query.data !== undefined`)
  — render that cached data with an `OfflineBanner`, not a bare error.
- Mutations (`useSaveProperty`, `useRemoveSavedProperty`) call
  `queryClient.invalidateQueries` on the relevant key in `onSuccess`.
- Anything that hits the network (Nominatim, localStorage-backed stores)
  lives in `src/lib/`, imported by the hook — hooks don't inline `fetch`
  calls themselves.
